  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b85\u0bae\u0bc8\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0b9c\u0bbf\u0bb0 ?\u00a0\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0b95\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bbf \u0b85\u0bb0\u0b9a\u0bbe\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b85\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bae\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0b95\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0b95\u0bb2 \u0b85\u0bb0\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b95\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b85\u0bae\u0bc8\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Will Vajira become a minister? Ministry for all political parties that are part of a multi-party government",
      "author": "Digital Desk 5",
      "body_lines": [
        "United National Party Secretary Vajira Abeywardhana will be sworn in as a Member of Parliament on the 27th. After that, he is expected to be sworn in as a cabinet minister.",
        "Ranil Wickremesinghe, who was elected to Parliament through the United National Party's national list, was elected as the 8th President through a secret ballot held in Parliament on the 20th.",
        "Subsequently, he resigned as a Member of Parliament after taking the oath of office as the President on the 21st. The Secretary General of the Parliament informed the National Elections Commission last week about the vacancy of the Member of Parliament.",
        "The National Elections Commission issued a gazette notification last week to confirm the nomination of United National Party Secretary Vajira Abeywardena's name to the National Elections Commission.",
        "Accordingly, Vajira Abeywardhana will take the oath of office as a member of Parliament in the upcoming Parliament session on the 27th.",
        "Negotiations have been carried out under the leadership of the President to bring together all the political parties that are members of the Parliament to establish an all-party government in a couple of weeks. It is expected to form a cabinet comprising 30 ministries.",
        "It is also known that it has been decided to give ministries to all the political parties that are part of the all-party government."
      ],
